  "prompt": "What did you do before a day before JEE advanced?",
  "response": "Here are some steps you might consider taking the day before the JEE Advanced exam to prepare effectively:\n\n1. **Review Important Concepts**: Go through important formulas, equations, and key concepts from Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics. Avoid starting any new topics.\n\n2. **Solve Few Sample Problems**: Work on a few important or favorite problems. This could boost your confidence and help you stay in the problem-solving mode.\n\n3. **Rest and Relax**: Ensure you get proper rest and relaxation. Overworking or stressing too much might hamper your performance.\n\n4. **Healthy Eating**: Maintain a healthy diet. Avoid eating junk food to stay in good physical condition.\n\n5. **Hydrate Well**: Drink enough water to stay hydrated.\n\n6. **Preparation of Essentials**: Gather all necessary items for the exam day, such as admit card, ID proof, required stationery (pens, pencils, erasers, etc.), and any other specified documents.\n\n7. **Visualize the Exam Day**: Mentally prepare yourself for the exam day scenario to ease any anxiety. Visualizing yourself confidently solving problems can be a part of positive reinforcement.\n\n8. **Avoid Excessive Studying**: Last-minute cramming is usually counterproductive. Ensure a calm mind by promising yourself that your preparation is already sufficient.\n\n9. **Sleep Well**: A good night\u2019s sleep can enhance your mental and physical performance for the exam day.\n\nFollowing these steps can help ensure you are well-prepared and in the right frame of mind to tackle the JEE Advanced exam effectively.",
